==Swedish==
====Etymology====
Cognates with German ''[[Dorf]]'' and Dutch ''[[dorp]]''

===Noun===
'''torp'''

#(''before 16:th century''): Solitaire [[farm]], distant from other settlements
#(''16:th century''): ''Officially defined'' as a very small farm
#(''17:th century to early 20:th century''): A small farm, rented from a larger land owner, and where the rent was payed through work on the owner's land (''[[dagsverken]]'')
#(''after the 1940's''): A small [[cottage]] on the [[countryside]]

